#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:2
msgid "Motion Mounting"
msgstr "Montaje de Movimiento"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:4
msgid ""
"When mounting a mechanism, it is important to know how to transfer power to "
"it. There are many ways of accomplishing this using an axle."
msgstr ""
"Al montar un mecanismo, es importante saber cómo transferirle potencia. Hay "
"muchas formas de conseguirlo utilizando un eje."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:7
#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:12
msgid "Live Axle"
msgstr "Eje vivo"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:9
#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:35
#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:58
msgid "Term"
msgstr "Término"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:14
msgid ""
"The simplest method of power transmission is called \"Live Axle\". In this "
"case, the mechanism is physically mounted on a powered axle: **when the axle"
" turns, the mechanism turns with it**. The mechanism on the axle generally "
"is mounted to a hub or pattern adaptor which transmits power from the axle. "
"For this reason, live axle is generally recommended when powering multiple "
"things together on one axle."
msgstr ""
"El método más sencillo de transmisión de potencia se denomina \"eje motor\"."
" En este caso, el mecanismo está montado físicamente sobre un eje accionado:"
" **Cuando el eje gira, el mecanismo gira con él**. El mecanismo en el eje "
"generalmente está montado en un buje o adaptador de patrón que transmite la "
"potencia desde el eje. Por esta razón, generalmente se recomienda el eje "
"accionado cuando se accionan varias cosas juntas en un eje."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:16
msgid ""
"This method of power transmission is most commonly used on mechanisms that "
"are mounted directly on a motor, as well as some mechanisms like intakes."
msgstr ""
"Este método de transmisión de potencia es el más utilizado en los mecanismos"
" que se montan directamente sobre un motor, así como en algunos mecanismos "
"como los intakes."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:19
#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:43
#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:66
msgid "Advantages"
msgstr "Ventajas"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:21
msgid "Simplest power transmission to build"
msgstr "La transmisión de potencia más sencilla de construir"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:22
msgid "Buildable with any COTS system"
msgstr "Construible con cualquier sistema COTS"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:23
msgid "Can power several mechanisms on the same axle together easily"
msgstr "Puede accionar varios mecanismos del mismo eje a la vez con facilidad"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:24
msgid "Can be used directly off of a motor shaft"
msgstr "Puede utilizarse directamente del eje de un motor"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:27
#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:50
#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:71
msgid "Disadvantages"
msgstr "Desventajas"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:29
msgid ""
"Can physically take up more space (bearings needed on either side of a "
"shaft)"
msgstr ""
"Puede ocupar físicamente más espacio (rodamientos necesarios a ambos lados "
"de un eje)"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:33
#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:38
msgid "Dead Axle"
msgstr "Eje muerto"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:40
msgid ""
"Another form of power transmission is called \"Dead Axle\". In a dead axle "
"setup, the mechanism is mounted on a fixed axle via bearings: **it is free "
"to spin around the axle**. This method requires the power transmission to be"
" physically bolted to the mechanism, because the axle itself will not "
"rotate. For this reason, dead axle is generally recommended when powering "
"one thing that is between two plates, as the axle itself can serve as a "
"standoff to provide support between the plates."
msgstr ""
"Otra forma de transmisión de potencia se denomina \"eje muerto\". En una "
"configuración de eje muerto, el mecanismo está montado sobre un eje fijo "
"mediante rodamientos: **Es libre de girar alrededor del eje**. Este método "
"requiere que la transmisión de potencia esté físicamente atornillada al "
"mecanismo, ya que el propio eje no girará. Por esta razón, el eje muerto se "
"recomienda generalmente cuando se acciona una cosa que está entre dos "
"placas, ya que el propio eje puede servir como un separador para "
"proporcionar apoyo entre las placas."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:45
msgid "Simple power transmission with custom building"
msgstr "Transmisión de potencia sencilla con construcción a medida"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:46
msgid "Axle can be used as a standoff support between different plates"
msgstr ""
"El eje puede utilizarse como soporte de separación entre diferentes placas"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:47
msgid "Can require less parts then a live axle setup"
msgstr "Puede requerir menos piezas que una configuración de eje vivo"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:52
msgid "Harder to transmit power over a long shaft"
msgstr "Es más difícil transmitir potencia a través de un eje largo"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:53
msgid "Usually limited to powering mechanisms between two parallel plates"
msgstr ""
"Normalmente se limita a accionar mecanismos entre dos placas paralelas"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:56
msgid "Zombie Axle (Coaxial)"
msgstr "Eje Zombie (Coaxial)"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:61
msgid "Zombie Axle"
msgstr "Eje Zombie"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:63
msgid ""
"Zombie axle is when one shaft serves as a dead axle for one mechanism and a "
"live axle for another mechanism. This means **one mechanism is mounted on "
"the shaft via bearings, but the shaft is free to rotate independently to "
"power a second mechanism**. This setup can be used to transmit power to two "
"things using the same revolution point, making it easy to power mechanisms "
"like arms with intakes, or suspension drivetrain pods. Zombie Axle is only "
"recommended when two mechanisms must be powered coaxially to each other."
msgstr ""
"Se habla de eje zombie cuando un eje sirve de eje muerto para un mecanismo y"
" de eje vivo para otro mecanismo. Esto significa que **un mecanismo está "
"montado en el eje a través de rodamientos, pero el eje es libre de girar de "
"forma independiente para alimentar un segundo mecanismo**. Esta "
"configuración se puede utilizar para transmitir potencia a dos cosas "
"utilizando el mismo punto de revolución, por lo que es fácil de alimentar "
"mecanismos como brazos con intakes, o cápsulas de suspensión del chasis. El "
"eje zombie sólo se recomienda cuando dos mecanismos deben ser alimentados "
"coaxialmente entre sí."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:68
msgid ""
"Only power transmission method that can power two mechanisms on the same "
"revolution point"
msgstr ""
"Único método de transmisión de potencia que puede accionar dos mecanismos en"
" el mismo punto de revolución."

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:73
msgid "Has the disadvantages of both live and dead axle"
msgstr "Tiene las desventajas del eje vivo y del eje muerto"

#: ../../gm0/source/docs/common-mechanisms/power-transmission/motion-mounting.rst:74
msgid "More mechanically complex"
msgstr "Mayor complejidad mecánica"
